# MEMORY — {{user.name}}

Long-term, persistent memory. Only write here when explicitly asked ("remember this", "don't forget", "log this", "save this", "make a note"). Short-term notes go to `memory/short-term/`.

Entries should be **situational**, not just factual. Include when it was learned and why it matters.

---

## Active Context

_What is on my mind right now — current focus, season of work, what I'm trying to ship or resolve. Fill in as the weeks evolve._

---

## People & Relationships

_Patterns about how I work with specific people or groups. Context that doesn't fit in a single person file. Linked via `[[wiki-links]]` to entries in `knowledge/people/`._

---

## Architecture & System Decisions

_How this AI-OS is wired, notable configuration choices, tools connected, and non-obvious conventions I want the agent to respect._

---

## Products & Projects

_High-level facts about what I'm building or running — stable, long-lived context. Project-specific detail belongs in each project's `projects/[project]/MEMORY.md`._

---

## Market & Competitive Intel

_Facts about my market, customers, and competitors that stay true across sessions. Fast-moving intel belongs in `knowledge/market/`._

---

## Operations & Infrastructure

_Tools, accounts, workflows, and infrastructure the agent should know exist (without credentials). Calendars, inboxes, CRMs, billing, deployment targets._

---

## Personal & Legal

_Anything personal or legal that persistent context should carry — working hours, time zones, entities I operate through, compliance boundaries._

---

## Content & Brand

_Durable facts about my voice, channels, and brand. Evolving brand assets and guidelines live in `voice/`._
